%html{:lang => "en"}
  %head
    %meta{:content => "text/html; charset=UTF-8", "http-equiv" => "content-type"}/
  %body
    %div{"data-role" => "page"}
      %div{"data-role" => "header"}
        %h1 jQuery.browser
      %div{"data-role" => "content", "data-theme" => "c", :id => "jQuery.browser1"}
        %h2.jq-clearfix.roundTop.section-title
          %span.name jQuery.browser
          %span.returns
            Returns:
            %a.return{:href => "http://docs.jquery.com/Types#Map"} Map
        .entry-details
          %p.desc
            %strong> Description:
            We recommend against using this property, please try to use feature detection instead (see jQuery.support). Contains flags for the useragent, read from navigator.userAgent. While jQuery.browser will not be removed from future versions of jQuery, every effort to use jQuery.support and proper feature detection should be made.
          %ul.signatures
            %li.signature{:id => "jQuery.browser"}
              %h4.name
                %span.versionAdded>
                  version added:
                  %a{:href => "/category/version/1.0/"} 1.0
                jQuery.browser
          .longdesc
            %p
              The
              %code $.browser
              property allows us to detect which web browser is accessing the page, as reported by the browser itself. It contains flags for each of the four most prevalent browser classes (Internet Explorer, Mozilla, Webkit, and Opera) as well as version information.
            %p Available flags are:
            %ul
              %li webkit (as of jQuery 1.4)
              %li safari (deprecated)
              %li opera
              %li msie
              %li mozilla
            %p
              This property is available immediately. It is therefore safe to use it to determine whether or not to call
              = succeed "." do
                %code $(document).ready()
              The
              %code $.browser
              property is deprecated in jQuery 1.3, but there are no immediate plans to remove it.
            %p
              Because
              %code $.browser
              uses
              %code navigator.userAgent
              to determine the platform, it is vulnerable to spoofing by the user or misrepresentation by the browser itself. It is always best to avoid browser-specific code entirely where possible. The
              %code $.support
              property is available for detection of support for particular features rather than relying on
              = succeed "." do
                %code $.browser
          %h3 Examples:
          #entry-examples.entry-examples
            #example-0
              %h4
                Example:
                %span.desc Show the browser info.
              %pre
                %code.example.demo-code
                  :preserve
                    &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                    &lt;html&gt;
                    &lt;head&gt;
                      &lt;style&gt;
                      p { color:green; font-weight:bolder; margin:3px 0 0 10px; }
                      div { color:blue; margin-left:20px; font-size:14px; }
                      span { color:red; }
                      &lt;/style&gt;
                      &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                    &lt;/head&gt;
                    &lt;body&gt;
                    	&lt;p&gt;Browser info:&lt;/p&gt;
                    &lt;script&gt;
                        jQuery.each(jQuery.browser, function(i, val) {
                          $("&lt;div&gt;" + i + " : &lt;span&gt;" + val + "&lt;/span&gt;")
                                    .appendTo(document.body);
                        });&lt;/script&gt;
                    &lt;/body&gt;
                    &lt;/html&gt;              %h4 Demo:
              .demo.code-demo
            #example-1
              %h4
                Example:
                %span.desc Returns true if the current useragent is some version of Microsoft's Internet Explorer.
              %pre
                %code.example $.browser.msie
            #example-2
              %h4
                Example:
                %span.desc Alerts "this is webkit!" only for webkit browsers
              %pre
                %code.example
                  :preserve
                    if ($.browser.webkit) {
                        alert("this is webkit!");
                     }            #example-3
              %h4
                Example:
                %span.desc Alerts "Do stuff for firefox 3" only for firefox 3 browsers.
              %pre
                %code.example
                  :preserve
                    jQuery.each(jQuery.browser, function(i, val) {
                       if(i=="mozilla" &amp;&amp; jQuery.browser.version.substr(0,3)=="1.9")
                          alert("Do stuff for firefox 3")
                     });            #example-4
              %h4
                Example:
                %span.desc Set a CSS property to specific browser.
              %pre
                %code.example
                  :preserve
                    jQuery.each(jQuery.browser, function(i) {
                       if($.browser.msie){
                          $("#div ul li").css("display","inline");
                       }else{
                          $("#div ul li").css("display","inline-table");
                       }
                     });      %div{"data-role" => "content", "data-theme" => "c", :id => "jQuery.browser.version2"}
        %h2.jq-clearfix.roundTop.section-title
          %span.name jQuery.browser.version
          %span.returns
            Returns:
            %a.return{:href => "http://docs.jquery.com/Types#String"} String
        .entry-details
          %p.desc
            %strong> Description:
            The version number of the rendering engine for the user's browser.
          %ul.signatures
            %li.signature{:id => "jQuery.browser.version"}
              %h4.name
                %span.versionAdded>
                  version added:
                  %a{:href => "/category/version/1.1.3/"} 1.1.3
                jQuery.browser.version
          .longdesc
            %p Here are some typical results:
            %ul
              %li Internet Explorer: 6.0, 7.0
              %li Mozilla/Firefox/Flock/Camino: 1.7.12, 1.8.1.3, 1.9
              %li Opera: 9.20
              %li Safari/Webkit: 312.8, 418.9
            %p Note that IE8 claims to be 7 in Compatibility View.
          %h3 Examples:
          #entry-examples.entry-examples
            #example-0
              %h4
                Example:
                %span.desc Returns the browser version.
              %pre
                %code.example.demo-code
                  :preserve
                    &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                    &lt;html&gt;
                    &lt;head&gt;
                      &lt;style&gt;
                      p { color:blue; margin:20px; }
                      span { color:red; }
                      &lt;/style&gt;
                      &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                    &lt;/head&gt;
                    &lt;body&gt;
                    	&lt;p&gt;
                      &lt;/p&gt;
                    &lt;script&gt;
                    
                        $("p").html("The browser version is: &lt;span&gt;" +
                                    jQuery.browser.version + "&lt;/span&gt;");
                    &lt;/script&gt;
                    &lt;/body&gt;
                    &lt;/html&gt;              %h4 Demo:
              .demo.code-demo
            #example-1
              %h4
                Example:
                %span.desc Alerts the version of IE that is being used
              %pre
                %code.example
                  :preserve
                    if ( $.browser.msie ) {
                      alert( $.browser.version );
                    }            #example-2
              %h4
                Example:
                %span.desc Often you only care about the "major number," the whole number. This can be accomplished with JavaScript's built-in parseInt() function:
              %pre
                %code.example
                  :preserve
                    
                    if (jQuery.browser.msie) {
                      alert(parseInt(jQuery.browser.version));
                    }
